          "author": 0,
          "author_avatar_urls": {
            "24": "https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/2379641e73e3046a64e070f0891b72e055f5be1e1f99661775c76fee0172baa2?s=24&r=g",
            "48": "https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/2379641e73e3046a64e070f0891b72e055f5be1e1f99661775c76fee0172baa2?s=48&r=g",
            "96": "https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/2379641e73e3046a64e070f0891b72e055f5be1e1f99661775c76fee0172baa2?s=96&r=g"
          },
          "author_name": "Tristan Velloza Kildaire",
          "author_url": "https://deavmi.assigned.network",
          "content": {
            "rendered": "<p>Got it working.<br />\nFirstly, need to still publish the port for Docker firewalling reasons, so I had to add:</p>\n<p>&#8220;`yaml<br />\nports:<br />\n     # Port i want acessible<br />\n     &#8211; 3000/tcp<br />\n&#8220;`</p>\n<p>Secondly, having a mix of networks in `networks:` didn&#8217;t help. I removed those; only then did it seem to work.</p>\n<p>I haven&#8217;t remove ip6tables for this either, kept that there as it can still be useful for cases where I don&#8217;t do this `routed` mode.</p>\n"
          },
          "date": "2025-10-15T20:41:09",
          "id": 1855,
          "link": "https://www.daryllswer.com/how-to-configure-routed-ipv6-in-docker/#comment-1855",
          "parent": 1854,
          "type": "comment"
        },
        {
          "_links": {
            "children": [
              {
                "embeddable": true,
